===Glyph origin===
{{Han etyl}}
{{liushu|p}} Outline of the chest, upper clothing. Compare to the upper part of {{zh-l|*文}}.

This pictogram 衣 can be split into two parts and hold another component (e.g., [[裹]], [[衮]], [[褱]], [[襄]], and [[𧝑]] as used in [[㞡]] > [[展]]). See also the top component of [[雜]].

===Etymology===
Traditionally derived from {{inh|zh|sit-pro|*w(y)a-t ~ wit|t=to wear; to clothe}}, whence {{ncog|my|ဝတ်|t=to wear}} ({{zh-ref|Schuessler, 2007}}), though the Baxter-Sagart reconstruction makes this phonetically suspect.

Pronunciation 2 ("to wear") is the [[exoactive]] form of pronunciation 1 ("garment; clothes") formed with the Old Chinese suffix [[Reconstruction:Old Chinese/-s|*-s]].

