===Etymology 1===
{{ja-kanjitab|yomi=k|ころも}}

{{IPAfont|⟨ko₂ro₂mo₂⟩}} → {{IPAfont|/koromo/}}

From {{inh|ja|ojp|sort=ころも|-}}. Appears in the ''{{w|Kojiki}}'' completed in 712 CE.  Attested in the ''{{w|Nihon Shoki}}'' of 720 with the phonetic spelling {{m|ojp||虚呂望}} {{IPAfont|⟨ko₂ro₂mo₂⟩}}.<ref name="NKDc">{{R:Nihon Kokugo Daijiten Concise}}</ref>

Ultimate derivation unclear.  A surface analysis might suggest that this is a compound of {{cog|ojp|-}} {{m|ojp||*転|pos={{IPAfont|*⟨ko₂ro₂⟩}}, “rolling, going around”}} + {{m|ojp|裳}} ({{IPAfont|⟨mo₂⟩}}, “skirt”).  However, the ''koro'' morpheme is not attested for any sense of concrete things until the 1200s, with Old Japanese attestations instead expressing the abstract sense of {{m|ja|頃|tr=koro||around a particular time, rough time period, season}}.

